2020-11-18 09:50:00-05:00,Twitter rolls out Fleets in a bid to make posting easier for users,"Summary List Placement Twitter is rolling out its stories feature ""Fleets"" globally this week, with the hopes of driving higher user engagement with the platform. Users can post Fleets that contain text, photos, videos, and reactions to tweets, and they will disappear after 24 hours, with sticker and livestreaming options available later. Twitter first began beta testing Fleets in Brazil back in March, before expanding to India, Italy, Japan, and South Korea. Following moves by Pinter est and LinkedIn , this is another social media platform launching ephemeral content capabilities to compete with Snapchat, Instagram, and Facebook this year. Twitter said that Fleets is an easier way for users to engage with the platform by reducing the pressures of posting. Twitter explained that some users feel uncomfortable posting tweets because they are too permanent and public, and that they don't enjoy the pressure of garnering retweets and likes. Fleets are supposed to alleviate these issues, as they cannot be retweeted.",TWTR,en,Business Insider
