2020-02-05 21:45:04-05:00,Twitter says it’ll start labelling ‘fake news’,"Bengaluru: Microblogging platform Twitter will start labelling, and in some cases, removing doctored or manipulated media that users share on its platform, from next month.Twitter will label the video or photo so that users know it has been doctored.However, in other cases, where the content might “impact public safety or cause serious harm,” Twitter said the video or photo would likely be removed.Twitter’s definition of “harm” goes beyond physical harm, like threats to a person’s or group’s physical safety or the risk of mass violence or civil unrest. Also included in the definition of “harm” are threats to the privacy or the ability of a person or group to freely express themselves or participate in civic events.Twitter will use three tests to decide how it will act on manipulated media. It will first confirm whether the media is synthetic or manipulated. It will then assess if the media is being shared in a deceptive manner. Finally, it will evaluate the potential for harm.Twitter made the announcement on Tuesday in a blog post.",TWTR,en,The Economic Times India
